title: Avalanches in the US, Counties by State, 1998-2008
name: Avalanches in the US, Counties by State, 1998-2008
description:
SHELDUS is a county-level data set for the U.S. on 18 different natural hazard event types along with property and crop losses, injuries, and fatalities for the period January 1960 through December 2005.

The database was compiled to examine spatial and temporal variability in historical hazard events and associated losses.U.S. county boundaries are adjusted to 2000 designations.

Counties and states were geocoded using http://www.gpsvisualizer.com/geocoder/ and then uploaded into GeoCommons. Multiple instances of the same counties occurred and to ensure that each point was recognized the latitude and longitudes were changed very slightly in excel to pick them up.

author.source: Sheldus, The Spatial Hazard Events and Losses Database for the United States
